the ruling sandinista party on 
thursday condemned the us congress approval of a 497 million 
humanitarian aid package for the contra rebels calling it a threat 
to the nicaraguan government 
the sandinista national liberation front on thursday issued a 
communique shortly after the senate vote saying its members 
repudiate the approval of these new funds by the us congress 
for the mercenary forces 
this has violated one more time the rights and the order of 
international justice and makes fun of the will of the central 
american presidents expressed in the document of costa del sol el 
salvador on feb 14 
after a twoday meeting at a resort outside the capital of san 
salvador the presidents of el salvador nicaragua guatemala 
costa rica and honduras agreed to come up with a plan by midmay to 
dismantle the rebel force 
nicaraguan president daniel ortega also promised to push for 
democratic reforms in his country and moved up elections by 10 
months to february 1990 
the statement signed by the fronts nine commanders called the 
humanitarian aid package threats by the us government to apply 
new forms of force against the leftist government 
the aid package was harshly criticized by the sandinista party 
and ortega president bush first unveiled the bipartisan plan to 
provide nonlethal aid to the estimated 11000 contra rebels who 
have been living with their families in honduran border camps since 
congress cut off military aid in february 1988 
ortega has charged any kind of aid to the contras interferes 
with regional peace efforts 
