princess anne and her husband mark phillips are 
1000 miles apart and are still silent on rumors of a rift in their 
15year marriage 
the 38yearold princess carried out a typically busy day of 
public engagements wednesday starting with the opening of a body 
scanning unit at wycombe general hospital and ending at a gala 
premiere of the american movie three fugitives to benefit the 
save the children fund 
her 40yearold husband left for spain on tuesday and visited 
the april fair in seville on wednesday 
royal navy commander timothy laurence 34 whose letters to anne 
touched off the wave of speculation remained out of sight 
wednesday at windsor castle where he was on duty as an aide to 
queen elizabeth ii 
rumors of trouble in the princess marriage have circulated 
since 1981 the latest round began thursday when the sun tabloid 
britains topselling paper with a circulation of 42 million 
reported it had received four letters sent to anne and stolen from 
her briefcase 
buckingham palace late saturday identified the letterwriter as 
laurence after a sunday paper said it would do so on tuesday the 
