governmentmandated austerity measures 
the measures imposed on this englishspeaking country of 750000 
on the northeast coast of south america included a 230 percent 
devaluation of guyanas dollar and the doubling of interest rates 
to 35 percent 
the measures were adopted by the government of president desmond 
hoyte to meet conditions set by the international monetary fund for 
a 19 billion aid package to revive the countrys economy which 
hasnt grown in 10 years 
fourteen protesters including two jesuit priests jailed tuesday 
