by police the arrests brought to 100 the number of people jailed 
for demonstrating against the measures since hoyte announced them 
on march 31 
while there has been no violence in the protests about 300 
department store workers who paralyzed the capitals commercial 
sector by staging a oneday walkout tuesday were fired when they 
returned to work wednesday authorities said 
the strike by 5000 bauxite workers 20000 sugar workers and 
800 university employees including professors entered its second 
week sugar and bauxite which is used to make aluminum are among 
the countrys main exports 
government spokesman christopher nascimento said union leaders 
calling for strikes were hurting themselves because in attempting 
to bring the economy to a halt they will not hurt the government 
but the nation as a whole 
with the measures guyanas dollar officially fell to 33 to the 
us dollar although it fetches up to 50 to a us dollar in the 
black market 
