inventors of the year for 1989 
david v goeddel william j kohr diane pennica and gordon a 
vehar researchers for genentech inc of south san francisco 
calif shared the honor presented annually by the intellectual 
property owners foundation which represents holders of patents 
copyrights and trademarks 
the team developed the drug known as tpa human tissue 
plasminogen activator it is used to help dissolve blood clots 
immediately following heart attacks 
the foundation which works to encourage innovation announced 
its awards at a news conference the winners of the top award will 
share a 4000 prize 
invention is the heart of american society commented robert 
p freese one of several other inventors also honored by the 
foundation 
among those listed as distinguished inventors of 1989 were 
freese and several coworkers who developed an optical computer 
storage disk capable of holding up to 1000 times more information 
than the popular floppy disks now in use 
developers of the disk were freese richard n gardner and 
thomas a rinehart of alphatronix inc at research triangle park 
nc and leslie h johnson of the 3m company in st paul minn 
others receiving distinguished inventor honors were 
james l ferguson of menlo park calif who invented a device 
