<TEXT>
the uss samuel b roberts crippled a 
year ago when it struck a mine in the persian gulf is back in the 
water for the conclusion of a 90 million repair job intended to 
make it better than new 
after six months in dry dock the 445foot guided missile 
frigate was refloated early this month at bath iron works where 
the complicated repairs are expected to be finished in october a 
month ahead of schedule 
the roberts and its sister ship the uss stark were damaged 
while on duty in the persian gulf during the war between iran and 
iraq the frigates are the first us warships to undergo repairs 
for battle damage since the korean war 
the stark was repaired at the ingalls shipyard in pascagoula 
miss at a cost of 829 million and rejoined the fleet last 
summer thirtyseven crew members were killed when the stark was 
hit by a missile fired from an iraqi jet on may 17 1987 
the 3700ton roberts was damaged on april 14 1988 when it hit 
an iranian mine while escorting reflagged kuwaiti tankers in the 
gulf ten sailors were injured 
the blast which nearly sank the roberts hit amidships below 
the waterline it demolished the engine room carved a 22foot gash 
in the hull and forced a repair job even more complex than the 
starks 
from the standpopair 
it was the type of damage sustained by a car that goes off a 
road and lands on a boulder destroying the entire drive train but 
leaving the external structure intact said cmdr john w townes 
iii who took over as skipper after the roberts was damaged 
the repairs to the stark and the roberts have been viewed as 
tests of both the shipbuilding industrys ability to reconstruct 
todays hightech warships and the nations political resolve in 
putting battledamaged vessels back in action swiftly and 
effectively navy and shipyard officials say 
supervisors at bath iron works which built the roberts three 
years ago say the task of repairing a modern warship and its 
computercontrolled propulsion system poses a unique technological 
challenge 
what has not been done before is putting an electronic engine 
room back together theres a world of difference between this 
engine room and the ones in the world war ii destroyers price 
said 
congress authorized 96 million for the repair job and biw says 
the costs are running 2 million to 3 million under budget the 
roberts cost roughly 350 million when it was built and outfitted 
