<TEXT>
president nicolae ceausescu announced 
wednesday that as of march 31 communist romania had repaid all its 
foreign debt the romanian state news agency agerpres reported 
in 1981 romanias foreign debt totaled about 11 billion but 
the bucharest government stopped almost all imports of western 
machinery and stepped up food exports for hard currency at the 
expense of serious food shortages at home 
by the end of 1988 romanias foreign debt had dropped to about 
2 billion 
there have been no indications however that authorities will 
raise living standards by importing badly needed consumer goods 
hard currency earnings are badly need to buy western machinery 
and equipment to modernize mostly outdated industrial 
installations most available resources probably will be used for 
that purpose 
ceasescu runs the most repressive nation in the soviet bloc and 
his efforts to rid it of foreign debt left romania financially 
strapped with food and power shortages further reducing a poor 
standard of living 
the presidents announcement came at the opening of a threeday 
session of the romanian communist partys policysetting central 
committee 
i wish to inform the plenary meeting the entire party and our 
entire people that at the end of march romania fully paid back its 
foreign debt agerpress quoted ceausescu as saying 
this is the outstanding result of our peoples work devoted to 
the countrys socioeconomic development it proves the might of 
the romanian socialist economy and opens wonderful prospects for 
implementation of the party program of building the multilaterally 
developed socialist society and romanias advance to communism 
agerpres said ceausescu on wednesday received a group of us 
business people representing over 50 companies that have trade 
relations with romania 
romania was deprived of most favored nation trading status on 
the us market last year because of its record on human rights 
if accorded the privilege romania would get the same terms as 
those granted now or in the future to any other nation 
ceasescu referred to the issue in his meeting with the 
americans saying there is only one problem awaiting an 
appropriate solution that is to apply the 1975 economic accord 
which also provides for the mutual granting of the most favored 
nation clause unconditionally on either side 
ceausescu said he would like to see twoway trade between the 
united states and romania reach the 2 billion mark annually 
agerpres reported he did not give the current figure 
