<TEXT>
japans trade surplus fell in march to 674 
billion its first decline in seven months from yearearlier 
levels the finance ministry announced thursday 
japanese exports had exceeded imports by 746 billion in march 
1988 and by 724 billion in february 1989 
the march figure brought japans trade surplus for fiscal 1988 
which ended march 31 to 7901 billion up from 7599 billion the 
previous year and the first increase in two years 
exports in fiscal 1988 increased 147 percent to 27294 
billion while imports rose 197 percent to 19392 billion the 
ministry said 
ministry officials said strong overseas demand for japanese 
products throughout the fiscal year had boosted exports especially 
of semiconductors computers cars and business machines 
they said imports remained brisk because of strong japanese 
domestic demand and included increased flows of foreign 
manufactured goods 
the ministry officials said the fiscal 1988 surplus rose mainly 
because of lower prices for oil japans largest import commodity 
in march exports climbed 169 percent from a year earlier to 
2655 billion while imports surged 298 percent to 1981 
billion the ministry said 
after seasonal adjustments the march surplus came to 557 
billion a sharp drop from 886 billion in february the ministry 
said 
the officials said imports surged in march as companies began 
importing in earnest after several months of restrained consumption 
due to emperor hirohitos death on jan 7 and funeral on feb 24 
importers also stepped up transactions before the end of the 
japanese fiscal year they said 
the trade surplus with the united states in march ballooned to 
413 billion from 340 billion a year earlier the ministry said 
exports grew 216 percent to 875 billion while imports rose 22 
percent to 462 billion 
for the fiscal year the trade surplus with the united states 
declined slightly to 4910 billion from 5084 billion in fiscal 
1987 exports to the united states rose 84 percent to 9260 
billion while imports grew 257 percent to 4350 billion the 
ministry said 
japans trade surplus with the european economic community in 
march fell to 167 billion from 193 billion a year earlier it 
said 
for the fiscal year japanese exports to the eec exceeded 
imports by 2232 billion up from 2011 billion the previous 
year exports rose 203 percent to 4780 billion while imports 
expanded by 299 percent to 2548 billion 
the surplus in trade with southeast asia in march grew to 234 
billion from 203 billion in march 1988 
japans trade surplus with the region for the fiscal year rose 
to 2037 billion from 1482 billion the previous year exports 
rose 239 percent to 6986 billion while imports grew 191 
percent to 4950 billion 
japan includes freight and insurance costs in its import 
figures but not in its exports 
