year when the deals had expired the companies said thursday 
general motors corp ford motor co and chrysler corp said 
cars and light trucks sold at an average daily rate of 34931 
during the april 110 period this year compared with a rate of 
27621 last year 
car sales soared 276 percent and sales of light trucks were up 
246 percent during the period 
late last month ford and gm announced new incentive packages 
featuring 29 percent interest on twoyear loans and increased 
rebates chrysler got into the fray april 3 going one step further 
to interestfree financing on twoyear loans for all of its cars 
while incentives surely contributed to some of the early april 
sales boom some of the increase is attributable to slow sales 
during the period last year incentives in effect during the first 
quarter of 1988 expired march 31 persuading consumers planning 
spring or summer purchases to make them earlier 
march and april typically are hot carselling months as 
americans get ready for summer vacations but march sales were 
lower than expected giving rise to the new incentive packages 
car and truck sales by the big three so far this year were 
running 69 percent behind last years pace going to a daily rate 
of 33068 vehicles compared with 35535 between jan 1 and april 
10 last year 
