bahamas and atlanta routes this week spokesman james ashlock said 
the company has concentrated on its most profitable routes mainly 
its northeastern shuttle service and latin american service in its 
strike schedule 
the airline has agreed to sell the shuttle to developer donald 
trump for 365 million 
only 200 of 3600 pilots have flown since their union joined the 
machinists strike 
the company still hopes to gain a federal appellate court order 
sending the pilots back to work even though us district judge 
edward b davis on wednesday reported to a appeals court that there 
was no evidence to support company claims the pilots are on an 
illegal strike 
