<TEXT>
a sale of striketorn eastern airlines 
increasingly is seen as the only way to resolve its deadlocked 
labor dispute according to many experts who also cautioned 
thursday that employees will discover they may have lost the fight 
no matter who ends up owning the carrier 
interested buyers following in the footsteps of peter v 
ueberroth are likely to demand at least the same 210 million in 
labor concessions included in his aborted takeover plan 
concessions are just the starting point for any further 
talks said paul tiffany a professor of management at the 
