board of directors rejected a 282 million offer from pa bergner 
amp co to merge the two midwest department store chains 
pa bergner a swissowned chain with headquarters in 
milwaukee sought to acquire carson pirie of chicago for at least 
20 a share in cash or an unspecified combination of cash stock 
and notes 
carsons board of directors has unanimously determined that it 
is not in the best interest of shareholders employees 
customers suppliers and other constituencies peter s willmott 
chairman president and chief executive of the company said in a 
letter to pa bergner 
during the last two years carson pirie has returned the 
company to retailing as its core business and provided carsons 
shareholders with a cash payment of more than 30 a share he 
wrote the best interests of carsons shareholders will be served 
by the company pursuing an independent course 
alan r anderson chairman and chief executive of pa bergner 
said he was disappointed with the decision 
our offer after all represents a 52 percent premium over the 
price at which carsons stock has traded during 1989 before the 
offer was made 
carson piries stock closed unchanged at 2137 a share 
wednesday on the new york stock exchange 
